Very neat and convenient restaurant. They serve large portions and for inexpensive prices. I loved the meals a lot and the staff members were very attentive and chatty. Recommended.
Good sushi place with a lot of roll selections. Fish are pretty fresh and service is good. Price is about the average, and place ambience is modern.
Good place and food. During the week lunch options are good deal. I had Alaska and Philadelphia maki and tuna and smoke salmon. The last one was the best. I will be back for more. 😋

Don't go here if you're in a rush. You won't be served in a rush.  The music, the ambiance, the food! It was all perfect. I had the beef ramen. Perfect blend of sesame and spice.  I look forward to coming again.
Go here weekly. Great service. Great sushi and ramen. Highly recommended. Love the wait staff and chefs.

Good local place for sushi.  Typically not very busy, so if you are looking for a quite place this is a good choice.  The ramen is unbelievably spicy, so be careful what level you order it at.  You can bring your own wine, but there is a $5 corkage fee.  The edamame is cold though. I like it better warm.  Staff is very nice.

Great service.....

The fish doesn't always seem to be the freshest ut they are still pretty good. Love this place been coming since they open.

Love this place so much that I became a regular Good prices Half off between 3 to 5 pm on some rolls and drinks Ramen is great Sashimi is good portions Not crowded Servers and sushi chefs are awesome

Great presentation, great ramen, side of the fire Phoenix sushi is recommended!

Love the Ramen for lunch. Five flavors to choose from, all very flavorful. Rolls are good too, tried the super white tuna with mango and one with jalapeno, both were very good. Service is quick and kind.
An adequate neighborhood eatery.  Not as creative or well prepared as some of the top sushi (not necessarily more expensive) places in the city.
Nice place. Love the sushi. Staff is very nice and professional.

I walked past this place and noticed the sign that had a beautiful ramen bowl on it and realized this might be the perfect restaurant for when my boyfriend and I are arguing over should we have sushi or ramen tonight. So the next time the debate popped up, I suggested the place, we went... and I wholly regretted it. The atmosphere is nice enough, although the old american pop-ie music is a little off putting it wasn't too loud when we sat outside and could ignore it, the server was nice and bubbly, my cocktail was perfect and the food was presented beautifully, but none of that can make up for the taste. My bf eats just about anything, so he finished off his sushi although he did say he wasn't interested in coming back after just the first bite. I couldn't even eat the ramen though, it looked so pretty but tasted like something a college student would make out of an instant noodle package, with corn and half of a hard boiled egg tossed in just 'cause. The 'meat' was just a slice of fat and gristle, the broth had no body or flavor to stick to the noodle, I'm going to mention again the egg was hard boiled and somehow grainy, and WHY is there corn in it? We ordered two roles of sushi, one bowl of ramen, one fruit smoothie and one cocktail, and the meal was 59$ I took not four bites out of the ramen before I returned it and they still charged me for it, only discounting it to half when I complained about it. I wouldn't pay 3$ to eat that ramen, much less the 13 they charge for it! Even the blueberry smoothie was bland, I don't know how you can mess up blueberry but these guys did it.
I had the tonkatsu ramen and it was delicious! The server was really nice and the atmosphere was very chill.

great place for lunch. nice cozy decor. tv to catch up on sports highlifhts is a plus. always a table available. and the sushi is great for $$. lunch specials are very reasonably priced. could do without the pop music on the sound system but its not very loud. had no trouble keeping a conversation going with 3 lunchmates.

The sushi here wasn't anything special. I checked it out because I had a groupon and I would not go back. The atmosphere was awkward and quiet. Also the women's bathroom only had a black light for a light and it also had a two way mirror so you could see the entire restaurant while you did your business!! This was the worst and most creepy bathroom I have ever used. I was completely disturbed and grossed out.
You can't beat the prices at Sushi Pink- the sushi is pretty good as well. I've never had to wait in line.
Top notch spicy tuna rolls here. Nice staff, nice bathrooms

I live in the West Loop and this is my go-to neighborhood sushi place. My husband and I come here probably at least once every two weeks and we always bring visiting friends and family here. Their Saturday happy-hour special (everything is 33% off from 11 AM to 3 PM) is PHENOMENAL. Excellent service, and I'm a huge fan of the glass jars of on-site filtered water. If you follow them on Facebook, they post some cool discounts and deals, too, like BOGOs. The ladies restroom is interesting - it's a black-lit room with a one-way mirror that faces into the dining area. All in all, though, this is my favorite local sushi place in the city.

Ok, it doesn't get better than 1/2 price martinis on Wednesdays. This quaint gem in the west loop area has the best volcano rolls in the city, We always have the same cute little server and she's always so sweet.
Great place for sushi in the west loop!!
great volcano roll!! it is a big roll and filling. it cost 13 bucks great place to stop before the hawks game  must go there

Got the animal and the spider.  Literally eating as I type, so far the animal is awesome. Real meat. And the roll is so long.... I got too much, oh well.  Spider is good as well. That's my go to for Sushi rolls currently.  Going to go all of next week and try as many different rolls as possible.

So minus the gnats... My husband said his role was one of the best he's ever had, better than Sushi Wabi's similar roll. My Rolls were fabulous, the steak and scallion and the shrimp tempura roll. Prices are better than anywhere in the area, but the portion sizes are smaller. So price is proportional to size. Skip the appetizers, not worth the $$, go straight for the rolls. Corny 90's love ballads music, but the place was pretty hoppin' for a Wednesday night. Nice overall neighborhood place!
Good price range on most of dishes and some innovate creations that differ from most of same-style places. The decoration is enjoyable with good lounge music. Friendly staff, nice experience overall.
